      <body>
         <p>Soteriology is the branch of Christian theology concerned with salvation. Its focus
            includes other key doctrines, such as Christ's atonement; human sin, repentance, faith,
            and conversion; justification, regeneration (new birth), and sanctification; grace and
            the means of grace; and eternal life. As many have noted, Wesley's overall theology is
            heavily focused on soteriology and the "holiness of heart" and "holiness of life."</p>
